    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-12-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-12-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="5" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d5">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram per cable.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Adams</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,
                                        <hi rend="italic">London,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-12-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 1, 1866</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Contract disavowed; no harm done. You will learn more by my letter due on
                            Wednesday. If my plan be adopted Morse would be of use here. He will
                            wait orders after you see my report.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>CHARLES FRANCIS ADAMS.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, Washington, D. C.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
